ANC presidential hopeful Cyril Ramaphosa’s campaign to lead Africa’s oldest liberation movement received a significant boost yesterday when he won the overwhelming support of the Eastern Cape province. According to media reports, Ramaphosa secured 423 branch nominations at the party’s provincial general council in East London yesterday, while his rival Nkosazana Dlamini Zuma managed 61. ANC treasurer-general Zweli Mkhize received 193 nominations for the position of deputy president while David Mabuza received 190 nominations. The province’s branches also nominated Gwede Mantashe as national chairperson (416 nominations), Senzo Mchunu as secretary general (408 nominations), Zingiswa Losi as deputy secretary general (172 nominations) and Paul Mashatile as treasurer-general, with 449 nominations.